---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Acknowledgements"
  description="Homages and references used in taeglich."
  renderH1={false}
  noindex={true}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p
        class="mb-2 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.3em] text-gray-400 uppercase"
      >
        Acknowledgements
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
        Acknowledgements & References
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
      <section>
        <p>
          taeglich is a project built on inspiration from decades of digital
          culture, games, and software. This page acknowledges the works and
          brands that have inspired the artifacts found here.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2
          class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold tracking-wider text-gray-900 uppercase"
        >
          Trademarks & Brands
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          All referenced names and brands are the property of their respective
          owners. Their mention here is for descriptive/reference purposes and
          does not imply any affiliation or endorsement.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-4 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <li>
            <strong>Tetris</strong>: Tetris is a trademark of Tetris Holding,
            LLC. The "BLOCKFALL" artifact is a homage to the classic
            falling-block puzzle genre popularized by Tetris.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>DOOM</strong>: DOOM is a trademark of id Software LLC, a
            ZeniMax Media company. References to the FPS genre are inspired by
            the technical and artistic legacy of the Doom series.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft Office Assistant</strong> ("paperclip helper"): The
            Office Assistant is a trademark of Microsoft Corporation. Future homages
            to desktop assistants are inspired by early office help systems.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2
          class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold tracking-wider text-gray-900 uppercase"
        >
          Open Source & Type
        </h2>
        <p>
          This project is made possible by the open-source community. Special
          thanks to the creators of:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm">
          <li>
            <a
              class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-gray-600"
              href="https://astro.build/"
              target="_blank">Astro</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-gray-600"
              href="https://tailwindcss.com/"
              target="_blank">Tailwind CSS</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            The various retro and modern typefaces provided via <a
              class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-gray-600"
              href="https://fontsource.org/"
              target="_blank">Fontsource</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-gray-400">
          License notices for included open-source software and fonts are
          provided where required.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
